            </p>
            <p>
              <strong class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">X-axis (bar width):</strong> Number of catalogued techniques targeting that band. Wider bars mean a larger attack surface. I0 is the widest because every technique that crosses the bio-digital boundary converges at this single point.
            </p>
            <p>
              <strong class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">The shape:</strong> The hourglass narrows at I0 not because it has fewer threats, but because it is a physical bottleneck. All neural data must pass through this point. The concentration of techniques at the waist is what makes it the highest-leverage target for both attack and defense.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

