      <section id="neurorights" class="mb-20">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] mb-6">6.5 Neurorights Mapping</h2>

        <div class="glass rounded-xl p-6 mb-8" style="border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent-tertiary);">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--color-accent-tertiary)] mb-2">From diagnosis to rights</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
            The Neural Impact Chain tells us what psychiatric harm a technique can cause. The neurorights mapping asks the next question: <strong>which fundamental rights does it violate?</strong>
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="prose mb-8">
          <p>
            Ienca &amp; Andorno (2017) proposed four neurorights: Mental Privacy, Cognitive Liberty, Mental Integrity, and Psychological Continuity. Chile enshrined them in law. The OECD endorsed them. But nobody had tested them against an actual threat taxonomy.
          </p>
          <p>
            Every technique in the TARA atlas is now mapped to the affected neurorights through a systematic, multi-layer process: UI category provides the primary signal, DSM-5-TR cluster adds overlays, and NISS vector components refine the result. This mapping is deterministic and reproducible &mdash; the same technique always maps to the same rights.
          </p>
          <p>
            Running {stats.totalTechniques} techniques through this process revealed that four rights are insufficient. Two additional rights were required to cover attack classes that the original taxonomy misses. These terms &mdash; Dynamical Integrity and Informational Disassociation &mdash; have been cross-validated against six established neurorights frameworks (Ienca &amp; Andorno 2017, Yuste/NeuroRights Foundation 2017, Chile Law 21.383, UNESCO 2025 Recommendation, Farahany 2023, Bublitz 2022) and confirmed absent from published neuroethics literature. They were discovered bottom-up through systematic threat analysis, not derived from philosophical reasoning:
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-8">
          {stats.neurorights.rights.map((r) => (
            <div class="glass-subtle rounded-lg p-4">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1">
                <span class={`inline-block px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-mono font-bold ${
                  r.id === 'DI' || r.id === 'IDA' ? 'bg-[var(--color-accent-tertiary)]/20 text-[var(--color-accent-tertiary)]' : 'bg-[var(--color-accent-primary)]/20 text-[var(--color-accent-primary)]'
