        </div>

        <div class="prose mb-8">
          <p>
            <strong>Right to Dynamical Integrity (DI)</strong> &mdash; Some attacks don't break neural function; they <em>retune</em> it. Gradual drift, neurofeedback falsification, and baseline adaptation poisoning reshape the brain's homeostatic equilibrium without triggering Mental Integrity violations in the traditional sense. {stats.neurorights.rights.find(r => r.id === 'DI')?.count} techniques affect this right &mdash; making it the third most commonly violated.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Right to Informational Disassociation (IDA)</strong> &mdash; Multi-modal biometric fusion attacks correlate neural data with gait, voice, typing rhythm, and physiological signals. Each stream alone is a privacy concern; fused, they create an identity signature that cannot be anonymized. IDA protects the right to consent to each data modality independently.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="glass rounded-xl p-6 mb-8" style="border-left: 4px solid #f59e0b;">
          <p class="font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-[var(--color-text-primary)] mb-2">Consent Complexity Index (CCI)</p>
